V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

22// Liftoff Frames.
23//
24// slot Frame
25// +--------------------+---------------------------
26// n+4 | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
27// n+3 | parameter n |
28// ... | ... |
29// 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
30// 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
31// 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
32// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
33// 1 | return addr (lr) |
34// 0 | previous frame (fp)|
35// -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
36// -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
37// -2 | instance |
38// -3 | feedback vector|
39// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
40// -4 | slot 0 | ^
41// -5 | slot 1 | |
42// | | Frame slots
43// | | |
44// | | v
45// | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
46// -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
47//
48
49inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
50
51inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
52 return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);
53}
54
55inline CPURegister GetRegFromType(const LiftoffRegister& reg, ValueKind kind) {
56 switch (kind) {
57 case kI32:
58 return reg.gp().W();
59 case kI64:
60 case kRef:
61 case kRefNull:
62 case kRtt:
63 return reg.gp().X();
64 case kF32:
65 return reg.fp().S();
66 case kF64:
67 return reg.fp().D();
68 case kS128:
69 return reg.fp().Q();
70 default:
71 UNREACHABLE();
72 }
73}
74
75inline CPURegList PadRegList(RegList list) {
76 if ((list.Count() & 1) != 0) list.set(padreg);
77 return CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, list);
78}
79
80inline CPURegList PadVRegList(DoubleRegList list) {
81 if ((list.Count() & 1) != 0) list.set(fp_scratch);
82 return CPURegList(kQRegSizeInBits, list);
83}
84
85inline CPURegister AcquireByType(UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
86 ValueKind kind) {
87 switch (kind) {
88 case kI32:
89 return temps->AcquireW();
90 case kI64:
91 case kRef:
92 case kRefNull:
93 return temps->AcquireX();
94 case kF32:
95 return temps->AcquireS();
96 case kF64:
97 return temps->AcquireD();
98 case kS128:
99 return temps->AcquireQ();
100 default:
101 UNREACHABLE();
102 }
103}

105template <typename T>
106inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
107 UseScratchRegisterScope* temps, Register addr,
108 Register offset, T offset_imm,
109 bool i64_offset = false, unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
110 if (!offset.is_valid()) return MemOperand(addr.X(), offset_imm);
111 Register effective_addr = addr.X();
112 if (offset_imm) {
113 effective_addr = temps->AcquireX();
114 assm->Add(effective_addr, addr.X(), offset_imm);
115 }
116 return i64_offset
117 ? MemOperand(effective_addr, offset.X(), LSL, shift_amount)
118 : MemOperand(effective_addr, offset.W(), UXTW, shift_amount);
119}
120
121// Compute the effective address (sum of |addr|, |offset| (if given) and
122// |offset_imm|) into a temporary register. This is needed for certain load
123// instructions that do not support an offset (register or immediate).
124// Returns |addr| if both |offset| and |offset_imm| are zero.
125inline Register GetEffectiveAddress(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
126 UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
127 Register addr, Register offset,
128 uintptr_t offset_imm,
129 bool i64_offset = false) {
130 if (!offset.is_valid() && offset_imm == 0) return addr;
131 Register tmp = temps->AcquireX();
132 if (offset.is_valid()) {
133 assm->Add(tmp, addr, i64_offset ? Operand(offset) : Operand(offset, UXTW));
134 addr = tmp;
135 }
136 if (offset_imm != 0) assm->Add(tmp, addr, offset_imm);
137 return tmp;
138}
139
140enum class ShiftDirection : bool { kLeft, kRight };
141
142enum class ShiftSign : bool { kSigned, kUnsigned };
143
144template <ShiftDirection dir, ShiftSign sign = ShiftSign::kSigned>
145inline void EmitSimdShift(LiftoffAssembler* assm, VRegister dst, VRegister lhs,
146 Register rhs, VectorFormat format) {
147 DCHECK_IMPLIES(dir == ShiftDirection::kLeft, sign == ShiftSign::kSigned);
148 DCHECK(dst.IsSameFormat(lhs));
149 DCHECK_EQ(dst.LaneCount(), LaneCountFromFormat(format));
150
151 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
152 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(format);
153 Register shift = dst.Is2D() ? temps.AcquireX() : temps.AcquireW();
154 int mask = LaneSizeInBitsFromFormat(format) - 1;
155 assm->And(shift, rhs, mask);
156 assm->Dup(tmp, shift);
157
158 if (dir == ShiftDirection::kRight) {
159 assm->Neg(tmp, tmp);
160 }
161
162 if (sign == ShiftSign::kSigned) {
163 assm->Sshl(dst, lhs, tmp);
164 } else {
165 assm->Ushl(dst, lhs, tmp);
166 }
167}
168
169template <VectorFormat format, ShiftSign sign>
170inline void EmitSimdShiftRightImmediate(LiftoffAssembler* assm, VRegister dst,
171 VRegister lhs, int32_t rhs) {
172 // Sshr and Ushr does not allow shifts to be 0, so check for that here.
173 int mask = LaneSizeInBitsFromFormat(format) - 1;
174 int32_t shift = rhs & mask;
175 if (!shift) {
176 if (dst != lhs) {
177 assm->Mov(dst, lhs);
178 }
179 return;
180 }
181
182 if (sign == ShiftSign::kSigned) {
183 assm->Sshr(dst, lhs, rhs & mask);
184 } else {
185 assm->Ushr(dst, lhs, rhs & mask);
186 }
187}
188
189inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
190 LiftoffRegister src) {
191 // AnyTrue does not depend on the number of lanes, so we can use V4S for all.
192 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(assm);
193 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(kFormat4S);
194 assm->Umaxp(temp, src.fp().V4S(), src.fp().V4S());
195 assm->Fmov(dst.gp().X(), temp.D());
196 assm->Cmp(dst.gp().X(), 0);
197 assm->Cset(dst.gp().W(), ne);
198}
199
200inline void EmitAllTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
201 LiftoffRegister src, VectorFormat format) {
202 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(assm);
203 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(ScalarFormatFromFormat(format));
204 assm->Uminv(temp, VRegister::Create(src.fp().code(), format));
205 assm->Umov(dst.gp().W(), temp, 0);
206 assm->Cmp(dst.gp().W(), 0);
207 assm->Cset(dst.gp().W(), ne);
208}
209
210inline CPURegister LoadToRegister(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
211 UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
212 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
213 if (src.is_reg()) {
214 return GetRegFromType(src.reg(), src.kind());
215 }
216 if (src.is_const()) {
217 if (src.kind() == kI32) {
218 if (src.i32_const() == 0) return wzr;
219 Register temp = temps->AcquireW();
220 assm->Mov(temp, src.i32_const());
221 return temp;
222 }
223 DCHECK_EQ(kI64, src.kind());
224 if (src.i32_const() == 0) return xzr;
225 Register temp = temps->AcquireX();
226 assm->Mov(temp, static_cast<int64_t>(src.i32_const()));
227 return temp;
228 }
229 DCHECK(src.is_stack());
230 CPURegister temp = AcquireByType(temps, src.kind());
231 assm->Ldr(temp, GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
232 return temp;
233}
234
235inline void StoreToMemory(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst,
236 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
237 if (src.kind() == kI16) {
238 DCHECK(src.is_reg());
239 assm->Strh(src.reg().gp(), dst);
240 return;
241 }
242 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{assm};
243 CPURegister src_reg = LoadToRegister(assm, &temps, src);
244 assm->Str(src_reg, dst);
245}

249int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
250 int offset = pc_offset();
251 InstructionAccurateScope scope(this, 1);
252 // Next we reserve the memory for the whole stack frame. We do not know yet
253 // how big the stack frame will be so we just emit a placeholder instruction.
254 // PatchPrepareStackFrame will patch this in order to increase the stack
255 // appropriately.
256 sub(sp, sp, 0);
257 return offset;
258}
259
260void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
261// The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
262// `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
263#ifdef __clang__
264 static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
265 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
266 kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
267 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
268#endif
269
270 // On ARM64, we must push at least {lr} before calling the stub, otherwise
271 // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it. So just set
272 // up the frame here.
273 EnterFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
274 LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
275 WasmValue(declared_function_index));
276 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
277}
278
279void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
280 int stack_param_delta) {
281 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
282 temps.Exclude(x16, x17);
283
284 // This is the previous stack pointer value (before we push the lr and the
285 // fp). We need to keep it to autenticate the lr and adjust the new stack
286 // pointer afterwards.
287 Add(x16, fp, 16);
288
289 // Load the fp and lr of the old frame, they will be pushed in the new frame
290 // during the actual call.
291#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
292 Ldp(fp, x17, MemOperand(fp));
293 Autib1716();
294 Mov(lr, x17);
295#else
296 Ldp(fp, lr, MemOperand(fp));
297#endif
298
299 temps.Include(x17);
300
301 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
302
303 // Shift the whole frame upwards, except for fp and lr.
304 // Adjust x16 to be the new stack pointer first, so that {str} doesn't need
305 // a temp register to materialize the offset.
306 Sub(x16, x16, stack_param_delta * 8);
307 int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params;
308 for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
309 ldr(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 8));
310 str(scratch, MemOperand(x16, i * 8));
311 }
312
313 // Set the new stack pointer.
314 mov(sp, x16);
315}
316
317void LiftoffAssembler::AlignFrameSize() {
318 // The frame_size includes the frame marker. The frame marker has already been
319 // pushed on the stack though, so we don't need to allocate memory for it
320 // anymore.
321 int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
322
323 static_assert(kStackSlotSize == kXRegSize,
324 "kStackSlotSize must equal kXRegSize");
325
326 // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
327 // Misalignment will cause a stack alignment fault.
328 int misalignment = frame_size % kQuadWordSizeInBytes;
329 if (misalignment) {
330 int padding = kQuadWordSizeInBytes - misalignment;
331 frame_size += padding;
332 max_used_spill_offset_ += padding;
333 }
334}
335
336void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
337 int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
338 bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
339 // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
340 // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
341 // for them anymore.
342 int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
343 // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector, and an unused
344 // slot for alignment.
345 if (feedback_vector_slot) {
346 frame_size = std::max(frame_size - 2 * kSystemPointerSize, 0);
347 }
348
349 // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
350 // Misalignment will cause a stack alignment fault.
351 DCHECK_EQ(frame_size, RoundUp(frame_size, kQuadWordSizeInBytes));
352
353 PatchingAssembler patching_assembler(zone(), AssemblerOptions{},
354 buffer_start_ + offset, 1);
355
356 if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
357 // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
358 // done with it.
359 DCHECK(IsImmAddSub(frame_size));
360 patching_assembler.PatchSubSp(frame_size);
361 return;
362 }
363
364 // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
365 // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
366 // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
367 // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
368 // replace the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} with a jump to OOL code that does
369 // this "extended stack check".
370 //
371 // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
372 // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
373 // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
374 // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
375 // large frame.
376
377 // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
378 // {pc_offset()}).
379 patching_assembler.b((pc_offset() - offset) >> kInstrSizeLog2);
380
381 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
382 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
383 // check in the condition code.
384 RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
385 Label continuation;
386 if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
387 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
388 Register stack_limit = temps.AcquireX();
389 LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
390 Add(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
391 Cmp(sp, stack_limit);
392 B(hs /* higher or same */, &continuation);
393 }
394
395 if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
396 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
397 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
398 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
399 for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
400 for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
401 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
402 Mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(), frame_size);
403 Add(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
404 Operand(stack_param_slots * kStackSlotSize +
405 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
406 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
407 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
408 } else {
409 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
410 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
411 // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
412 safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
413 if (v8_flags.debug_code) Brk(0);
414 }
415
416 bind(&continuation);
417
418 // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
419 // decrementing the SP; consult {MacroAssembler::Claim}.
420 Claim(frame_size, 1);
421
422 // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
423 // right after the reserved space for the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} (which
424 // is a branch now).
425 int func_start_offset = offset + kInstrSize;
426 b((func_start_offset - pc_offset()) >> kInstrSizeLog2);
427}

438int LiftoffAssembler::SlotSizeForType(ValueKind kind) {
439 // TODO(zhin): Unaligned access typically take additional cycles, we should do
440 // some performance testing to see how big an effect it will take.
441 switch (kind) {
442 case kS128:
443 return value_kind_size(kind);
444 default:
445 return kStackSlotSize;
446 }
447}

449bool LiftoffAssembler::NeedsAlignment(ValueKind kind) {
450 return kind == kS128 || is_reference(kind);

453void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
454 Label* ool_label,
455 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
456 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
457 Register budget_array = temps.AcquireX();
458
459 Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
460 if (instance_data == no_reg) {
461 instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the temp register.
462 LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
463 }
464
465 constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
466 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
467 ldr(budget_array, MemOperand{instance_data, kArrayOffset});
468
469 int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
470 // If the offset cannot be used in the operand directly, add it once to the
471 // budget_array to avoid doing that two times below.
472 if (!IsImmLSScaled(budget_arr_offset, 2 /* log2(sizeof(i32)) */) &&
473 !IsImmLSUnscaled(budget_arr_offset)) {
474 Add(budget_array, budget_array, budget_arr_offset);
475 budget_arr_offset = 0;
476 }
477
478 Register budget = temps.AcquireW();
479 MemOperand budget_addr{budget_array, budget_arr_offset};
480 ldr(budget, budget_addr);
481 // Make sure that the {budget_used} can be used as an immediate for SUB.
482 if (budget_used > 0xFFF000) {
483 budget_used = 0xFFF000; // 16'773'120
484 } else if (budget_used > 0xFFF) {
485 budget_used &= 0xFFF000;
486 }
487 DCHECK(IsImmAddSub(budget_used));
488 AddSub(budget, budget, Operand{budget_used}, SetFlags, SUB);
489 str(budget, budget_addr);
490 B(ool_label, mi);
491}
492
493Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
494 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
495 return fp;
496 }
497 LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
498 Label done, call_runtime;
499 Ldr(old_fp.gp(), MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
500 Cmp(old_fp.gp(),
501 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
502 B(eq, &call_runtime);
503 Mov(old_fp.gp(), fp);
504 jmp(&done);
505
506 bind(&call_runtime);
507 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
508 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
509 Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
510 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
511 if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
512 Mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
513 }
514 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
515
516 bind(&done);
517 return old_fp.gp();
518}
519
520void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
521 {
522 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
523 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
524 Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
525 Cmp(scratch,
526 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
527 }
528 Label done;
529 B(ne, &done);
530 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
531 for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
532 for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
533 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
534 Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
535 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
536 Mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
537 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
538 if (options().enable_simulator_code) {
539 // The next instruction after shrinking stack is leaving the frame.
540 // So SP will be set to old FP there. Switch simulator stack limit here.
541 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
542 temps.Exclude(x16);
543 LoadStackLimit(x16, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
544 hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
545 }
546 bind(&done);
547}

549void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
550 switch (value.type().kind()) {
551 case kI32:
552 Mov(reg.gp().W(), value.to_i32());
553 break;
554 case kI64:
555 Mov(reg.gp().X(), value.to_i64());
556 break;
557 case kF32:
558 Fmov(reg.fp().S(), value.to_f32());
559 break;
560 case kF64:
561 Fmov(reg.fp().D(), value.to_f64());
562 break;
563 default:
564 UNREACHABLE();
565 }
566}

569 Ldr(dst, liftoff::GetInstanceDataOperand());
570}

572void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTrustedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,

574 MemOperand src{src_addr, offset};
575 LoadTrustedPointerField(dst, src, tag);
576}
577
578void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
579 int offset, int size) {
580 DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
581 MemOperand src{instance, offset};
582 switch (size) {
583 case 1:
584 Ldrb(dst.W(), src);
585 break;
586 case 4:
587 Ldr(dst.W(), src);
588 break;
589 case 8:
590 Ldr(dst, src);
591 break;
592 default:
593 UNIMPLEMENTED();
594 }
595}

598 Register instance,
599 int offset) {
600 DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
601 LoadTaggedField(dst, MemOperand{instance, offset});
602}

608void LiftoffAssembler::ResetOSRTarget() {}

610enum class LoadOrStore : bool { kLoad, kStore };
611
612// The purpose of this class is to reconstruct the PC offset of a protected
613// instruction (load or store) that has just been emitted. We cannot simply
614// record the current PC offset before emitting the instruction, because the
615// respective helper function we call might emit more than one instruction
616// (e.g. to load an immediate into a register, or to get a constant pool
617// out of the way).
618//
619// Template arguments:
620// kLoadOrStore:
621// DCHECK that the detected protected instruction has the right type.
622// kExtraEmittedInstructions:
623// By default, we assume that when the destructor runs, the PC is right
624// behind the protected instruction. If additional instructions are expected
625// to have been emitted (such as a pointer decompression), specify their
626// number here.
627template <LoadOrStore kLoadOrStore, uint8_t kExtraEmittedInstructions = 0>
628class GetProtectedInstruction {
629 public:
630 GetProtectedInstruction(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
631 uint32_t* protected_instruction_pc)
632 : assm_(assm),
633 protected_instruction_pc_(protected_instruction_pc),
634 // First emit any required pools...
635 blocked_pools_scope_(assm, kReservedInstructions * kInstrSize),
636 // ...then record the PC offset before the relevant instruction
637 // sequence.
638 previous_pc_offset_(assm->pc_offset()) {}
639
640 ~GetProtectedInstruction() {
641 if (!protected_instruction_pc_) return;
642 *protected_instruction_pc_ =
643 assm_->pc_offset() - kInstrSize * (1 + kExtraEmittedInstructions);
644 if constexpr (kLoadOrStore == LoadOrStore::kLoad) {
645 DCHECK(assm_->InstructionAt(*protected_instruction_pc_)->IsLoad());
646 } else {
647 DCHECK(assm_->InstructionAt(*protected_instruction_pc_)->IsStore());
648 }
649 // Make sure {kReservedInstructions} was large enough.
650 DCHECK_LE(assm_->pc_offset() - previous_pc_offset_,
651 kReservedInstructions * kInstrSize);
652 USE(previous_pc_offset_);
653 }
654
655 private:
656 // For simplicity, we hard-code this value. We could make it a template
657 // argument if we needed more flexibility. It must be at least the maximum
658 // length of the instruction sequence emitted by the {LoadTaggedField} etc.
659 // helper functions below.
660 static constexpr int kReservedInstructions = 4;
661
662 LiftoffAssembler* assm_;
663 uint32_t* protected_instruction_pc_;
664 MacroAssembler::BlockPoolsScope blocked_pools_scope_;
665 int previous_pc_offset_;
666};
667
668void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTaggedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
669 Register offset_reg,
670 int32_t offset_imm,
671 uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
672 bool needs_shift) {
673 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
674 unsigned shift_amount = !needs_shift ? 0 : COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 2 : 3;
675 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
676 offset_imm, false, shift_amount);
677 DCHECK(!src_op.IsPostIndex()); // See MacroAssembler::LoadStoreMacroComplex.
678 constexpr uint8_t kDecompressionInstruction = COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 1 : 0;
679 GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kLoad, kDecompressionInstruction>
680 collect_protected_load(this, protected_load_pc);
681 LoadTaggedField(dst, src_op);
682}
683
684void LiftoffAssembler::LoadProtectedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
685 int32_t offset_imm) {
686 LoadProtectedPointerField(dst, MemOperand{src_addr, offset_imm});
687}
688
689void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFullPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
690 int32_t offset_imm) {
691 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
692 MemOperand src_op =
693 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, no_reg, offset_imm);
694 Ldr(dst.X(), src_op);
695}
696
697#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
698void LiftoffAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(Register dst,
699 Register src_addr,
700 int32_t offset_imm) {
701 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
702 MemOperand src_op =
703 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, no_reg, offset_imm);
704 MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(dst, src_op,
705 kWasmEntrypointTag);
706}
707#endif
708
709void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
710 Register offset_reg,
711 int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
712 LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
713 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
714 SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
715 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
716 Operand offset_op = offset_reg.is_valid() ? Operand(offset_reg.W(), UXTW)
717 : Operand(offset_imm);
718 // This is similar to {liftoff::GetMemOp}, but leaves {dst_addr} alone, and
719 // gives us a combined {offset_op}, which we need for the write barrier
720 // below. The 32-bit addition is okay because on-heap offsets don't get
721 // bigger than that.
722 if (offset_reg.is_valid() && offset_imm) {
723 Register effective_offset = temps.AcquireX();
724 Add(effective_offset.W(), offset_reg.W(), offset_imm);
725 offset_op = effective_offset;
726 }
727 {
728 GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kStore> collect_protected_store(
729 this, protected_store_pc);
730 StoreTaggedField(src, MemOperand(dst_addr.X(), offset_op));
731 }
732
733 if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
734
735 // The write barrier.
736 Label exit;
737 CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
738 kZero, &exit);
739 JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
740 CheckPageFlag(src, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
741 CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, offset_op, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
742 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
743 bind(&exit);
744}
745
746void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
747 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
748 LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
749 bool /* is_load_mem */, bool i64_offset,
750 bool needs_shift) {
751 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
752 unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
753 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
754 offset_imm, i64_offset, shift_amount);
755 DCHECK(!src_op.IsPostIndex()); // See MacroAssembler::LoadStoreMacroComplex.
756 GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kLoad> collect_protected_load(
757 this, protected_load_pc);
758 switch (type.value()) {
759 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
760 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
761 Ldrb(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
762 break;
763 case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
764 Ldrsb(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
765 break;
766 case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
767 Ldrsb(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
768 break;
769 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
770 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
771 Ldrh(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
772 break;
773 case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
774 Ldrsh(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
775 break;
776 case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
777 Ldrsh(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
778 break;
779 case LoadType::kI32Load:
780 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
781 Ldr(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
782 break;
783 case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
784 Ldrsw(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
785 break;
786 case LoadType::kI64Load:
787 Ldr(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
788 break;
789 case LoadType::kF32Load:
790 Ldr(dst.fp().S(), src_op);
791 break;
792 case LoadType::kF32LoadF16: {
793 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, FP16);
794 Ldr(dst.fp().H(), src_op);
795 Fcvt(dst.fp().S(), dst.fp().H());
796 break;
797 }
798 case LoadType::kF64Load:
799 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
800 break;
801 case LoadType::kS128Load:
802 Ldr(dst.fp().Q(), src_op);
803 break;
804 }
805}
806
807void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
808 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
809 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
810 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
811 bool /* is_store_mem */, bool i64_offset) {
812 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
813 MemOperand dst_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg,
814 offset_imm, i64_offset);
815 DCHECK(!dst_op.IsPostIndex()); // See MacroAssembler::LoadStoreMacroComplex.
816 GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kStore> collect_protected_store(
817 this, protected_store_pc);
818 switch (type.value()) {
819 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
820 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
821 Strb(src.gp().W(), dst_op);
822 break;
823 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
824 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
825 Strh(src.gp().W(), dst_op);
826 break;
827 case StoreType::kI32Store:
828 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
829 Str(src.gp().W(), dst_op);
830 break;
831 case StoreType::kI64Store:
832 Str(src.gp().X(), dst_op);
833 break;
834 case StoreType::kF32StoreF16: {
835 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, FP16);
836 Fcvt(src.fp().H(), src.fp().S());
837 Str(src.fp().H(), dst_op);
838 break;
839 }
840 case StoreType::kF32Store:
841 Str(src.fp().S(), dst_op);
842 break;
843 case StoreType::kF64Store:
844 Str(src.fp().D(), dst_op);
845 break;
846 case StoreType::kS128Store:
847 Str(src.fp().Q(), dst_op);
848 break;
849 }
850}
851
852namespace liftoff {
853#define __ lasm->
854
855inline Register CalculateActualAddress(LiftoffAssembler* lasm,
856 UseScratchRegisterScope& temps,
857 Register addr_reg, Register offset_reg,
858 uintptr_t offset_imm) {
859 DCHECK_NE(addr_reg, no_reg);
860 if (offset_reg == no_reg && offset_imm == 0) return addr_reg;
861 Register result = temps.AcquireX();
862 if (offset_reg == no_reg) {
863 __ Add(result, addr_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
864 } else {
865 __ Add(result, addr_reg, Operand(offset_reg));
866 if (offset_imm != 0) __ Add(result, result, Operand(offset_imm));
867 }
868 return result;
869}
870
871enum class Binop { kAdd, kSub, kAnd, kOr, kXor, kExchange };
872
873inline void AtomicBinop(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr,
874 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
875 LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
876 StoreType type, Binop op) {
877 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result};
878 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
879 Register store_result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
880
881 // {LiftoffCompiler::AtomicBinop} ensures that {result} is unique.
882 DCHECK(result.gp() != value.gp() && result.gp() != dst_addr &&
883 result.gp() != offset_reg);
884
885 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
886 Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
887 lasm, temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
888
889 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
890 CpuFeatureScope scope(lasm, LSE);
891 switch (op) {
892 case Binop::kAnd:
893 switch (type.value()) {
894 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
895 case StoreType::kI32Store8: {
896 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
897 Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
898 __ mvn(temp, value.gp().W());
899 __ ldclralb(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
900 break;
901 }
902 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
903 case StoreType::kI32Store16: {
904 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
905 Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
906 __ mvn(temp, value.gp().W());
907 __ ldclralh(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
908 break;
909 }
910 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
911 case StoreType::kI32Store: {
912 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
913 Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
914 __ mvn(temp, value.gp().W());
915 __ ldclral(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
916 break;
917 }
918 case StoreType::kI64Store: {
919 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
920 Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
921 __ mvn(temp, value.gp());
922 __ ldclral(temp, result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
923 break;
924 }
925 default:
926 UNREACHABLE();
927 }
928 break;
929 case Binop::kSub:
930 switch (type.value()) {
931 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
932 case StoreType::kI32Store8: {
933 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
934 Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
935 __ neg(temp, value.gp().W());
936 __ ldaddalb(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
937 break;
938 }
939 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
940 case StoreType::kI32Store16: {
941 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
942 Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
943 __ neg(temp, value.gp().W());
944 __ ldaddalh(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
945 break;
946 }
947 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
948 case StoreType::kI32Store: {
949 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
950 Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
951 __ neg(temp, value.gp().W());
952 __ ldaddal(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
953 break;
954 }
955 case StoreType::kI64Store: {
956 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
957 Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
958 __ neg(temp, value.gp());
959 __ ldaddal(temp, result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
960 break;
961 }
962 default:
963 UNREACHABLE();
964 }
965 break;
966#define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(op, instr) \
967 case Binop::op: \
968 switch (type.value()) { \
969 case StoreType::kI64Store8: \
970 case StoreType::kI32Store8: \
971 __ instr##b(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
972 break; \
973 case StoreType::kI64Store16: \
974 case StoreType::kI32Store16: \
975 __ instr##h(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
976 break; \
977 case StoreType::kI64Store32: \
978 case StoreType::kI32Store: \
979 __ instr(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
980 break; \
981 case StoreType::kI64Store: \
982 __ instr(value.gp(), result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
983 break; \
984 default: \
985 UNREACHABLE(); \
986 } \
987 break;
988 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kAdd, ldaddal)
989 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kOr, ldsetal)
990 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kXor, ldeoral)
991 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kExchange, swpal)
992#undef ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE
993 }
994 } else {
995 // Allocate an additional {temp} register to hold the result that should be
996 // stored to memory. Note that {temp} and {store_result} are not allowed to
997 // be the same register.
998 Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
999
1000 Label retry;
1001 __ Bind(&retry);
1002 switch (type.value()) {
1003 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1004 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1005 __ ldaxrb(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1006 break;
1007 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1008 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1009 __ ldaxrh(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1010 break;
1011 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1012 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1013 __ ldaxr(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1014 break;
1015 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1016 __ ldaxr(result.gp().X(), actual_addr);
1017 break;
1018 default:
1019 UNREACHABLE();
1020 }
1021
1022 switch (op) {
1023 case Binop::kAdd:
1024 __ add(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1025 break;
1026 case Binop::kSub:
1027 __ sub(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1028 break;
1029 case Binop::kAnd:
1030 __ and_(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1031 break;
1032 case Binop::kOr:
1033 __ orr(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1034 break;
1035 case Binop::kXor:
1036 __ eor(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1037 break;
1038 case Binop::kExchange:
1039 __ mov(temp, value.gp());
1040 break;
1041 }
1042
1043 switch (type.value()) {
1044 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1045 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1046 __ stlxrb(store_result.W(), temp.W(), actual_addr);
1047 break;
1048 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1049 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1050 __ stlxrh(store_result.W(), temp.W(), actual_addr);
1051 break;
1052 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1053 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1054 __ stlxr(store_result.W(), temp.W(), actual_addr);
1055 break;
1056 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1057 __ stlxr(store_result.W(), temp.X(), actual_addr);
1058 break;
1059 default:
1060 UNREACHABLE();
1061 }
1062
1063 __ Cbnz(store_result.W(), &retry);
1064 }
1065}
1066
1067#undef __
1068} // namespace liftoff
1069
1070void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
1071 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1072 LoadType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
1073 bool /* i64_offset */) {
1074 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1075 Register src_reg = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(this, temps, src_addr,
1076 offset_reg, offset_imm);
1077 switch (type.value()) {
1078 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
1079 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
1080 Ldarb(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1081 return;
1082 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
1083 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
1084 Ldarh(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1085 return;
1086 case LoadType::kI32Load:
1087 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
1088 Ldar(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1089 return;
1090 case LoadType::kI64Load:
1091 Ldar(dst.gp().X(), src_reg);
1092 return;
1093 default:
1094 UNREACHABLE();
1095 }
1096}
1097
1098void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
1099 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
1100 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
1101 bool /* i64_offset */) {
1102 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1103 Register dst_reg = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(this, temps, dst_addr,
1104 offset_reg, offset_imm);
1105 switch (type.value()) {
1106 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1107 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1108 Stlrb(src.gp().W(), dst_reg);
1109 return;
1110 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1111 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1112 Stlrh(src.gp().W(), dst_reg);
1113 return;
1114 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1115 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1116 Stlr(src.gp().W(), dst_reg);
1117 return;
1118 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1119 Stlr(src.gp().X(), dst_reg);
1120 return;
1121 default:
1122 UNREACHABLE();
1123 }
1124}

1174
1175void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
1176 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1177 LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
1178 StoreType type, bool /* i64_offset */) {
1179 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, expected, new_value};
1180 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
1181
1182 Register result_reg = result.gp();
1183 if (pinned.has(result)) {
1184 result_reg = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1185 }
1186
1187 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1188
1189 Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1190 this, temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1191
1192 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
1193 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LSE);
1194 switch (type.value()) {
1195 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1196 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1197 if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1198 mov(result.gp().W(), expected.gp().W());
1199 }
1200 casalb(result.gp().W(), new_value.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1201 break;
1202 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1203 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1204 if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1205 mov(result.gp().W(), expected.gp().W());
1206 }
1207 casalh(result.gp().W(), new_value.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1208 break;
1209 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1210 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1211 if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1212 mov(result.gp().W(), expected.gp().W());
1213 }
1214 casal(result.gp().W(), new_value.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1215 break;
1216 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1217 if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1218 mov(result.gp().X(), expected.gp().X());
1219 }
1220 casal(result.gp().X(), new_value.gp().X(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1221 break;
1222 default:
1223 UNREACHABLE();
1224 }
1225 } else {
1226 Register store_result = temps.AcquireW();
1227
1228 Label retry;
1229 Label done;
1230 Bind(&retry);
1231 switch (type.value()) {
1232 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1233 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1234 ldaxrb(result_reg.W(), actual_addr);
1235 Cmp(result.gp().W(), Operand(expected.gp().W(), UXTB));
1236 B(ne, &done);
1237 stlxrb(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1238 break;
1239 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1240 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1241 ldaxrh(result_reg.W(), actual_addr);
1242 Cmp(result.gp().W(), Operand(expected.gp().W(), UXTH));
1243 B(ne, &done);
1244 stlxrh(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1245 break;
1246 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1247 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1248 ldaxr(result_reg.W(), actual_addr);
1249 Cmp(result.gp().W(), Operand(expected.gp().W(), UXTW));
1250 B(ne, &done);
1251 stlxr(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1252 break;
1253 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1254 ldaxr(result_reg.X(), actual_addr);
1255 Cmp(result.gp().X(), Operand(expected.gp().X(), UXTX));
1256 B(ne, &done);
1257 stlxr(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().X(), actual_addr);
1258 break;
1259 default:
1260 UNREACHABLE();
1261 }
1262
1263 Cbnz(store_result.W(), &retry);
1264 Bind(&done);
1265 }
1266
1267 if (result_reg != result.gp()) {
1268 mov(result.gp(), result_reg);
1269 }
1270}
1271
1272void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicFence() { Dmb(InnerShareable, BarrierAll); }
1273
1274void LiftoffAssembler::LoadCallerFrameSlot(LiftoffRegister dst,
1275 uint32_t caller_slot_idx,
1276 ValueKind kind) {
1277 int32_t offset = (caller_slot_idx + 1) * LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize;
1278 Ldr(liftoff::GetRegFromType(dst, kind), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1279}
1280
1281void LiftoffAssembler::StoreCallerFrameSlot(LiftoffRegister src,
1282 uint32_t caller_slot_idx,
1283 ValueKind kind,
1284 Register frame_pointer) {
1285 int32_t offset = (caller_slot_idx + 1) * LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize;
1286 Str(liftoff::GetRegFromType(src, kind), MemOperand(frame_pointer, offset));
1287}
1288
1289void LiftoffAssembler::LoadReturnStackSlot(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset,
1290 ValueKind kind) {
1291 Ldr(liftoff::GetRegFromType(dst, kind), MemOperand(sp, offset));
1292}
1293
1294void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1295 ValueKind kind) {
1296 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1297 CPURegister scratch = liftoff::AcquireByType(&temps, kind);
1298 Ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1299 Str(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1300}
1301
1302void LiftoffAssembler::Move(Register dst, Register src, ValueKind kind) {
1303 if (kind == kI32) {
1304 Mov(dst.W(), src.W());
1305 } else {
1306 DCHECK(kI64 == kind || is_reference(kind));
1307 Mov(dst.X(), src.X());
1308 }
1309}
1310
1311void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1312 ValueKind kind) {
1313 if (kind == kF32) {
1314 Fmov(dst.S(), src.S());
1315 } else if (kind == kF64) {
1316 Fmov(dst.D(), src.D());
1317 } else {
1318 DCHECK_EQ(kS128, kind);
1319 Mov(dst.Q(), src.Q());
1320 }
1321}
1322
1323void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1324 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1325 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1326 Str(liftoff::GetRegFromType(reg, kind), dst);
1327}
1328
1329void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1330 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1331 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1332 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1333 CPURegister src = CPURegister::no_reg();
1334 switch (value.type().kind()) {
1335 case kI32:
1336 if (value.to_i32() == 0) {
1337 src = wzr;
1338 } else {
1339 src = temps.AcquireW();
1340 Mov(src.W(), value.to_i32());
1341 }
1342 break;
1343 case kI64:
1344 if (value.to_i64() == 0) {
1345 src = xzr;
1346 } else {
1347 src = temps.AcquireX();
1348 Mov(src.X(), value.to_i64());
1349 }
1350 break;
1351 default:
1352 // We do not track f32 and f64 constants, hence they are unreachable.
1353 UNREACHABLE();
1354 }
1355 Str(src, dst);
1356}
1357
1358void LiftoffAssembler::Fill(LiftoffRegister reg, int offset, ValueKind kind) {
1359 MemOperand src = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1360 Ldr(liftoff::GetRegFromType(reg, kind), src);
1361}
1362
1363void LiftoffAssembler::FillI64Half(Register, int offset, RegPairHalf) {
1364 UNREACHABLE();
1365}
1366
1367void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1368 // Zero 'size' bytes *below* start, byte at offset 'start' is untouched.
1369 DCHECK_LE(0, start);
1370 DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1371 DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 4);
1372 RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1373
1374 int max_stp_offset = -start - size;
1375 // We check IsImmLSUnscaled(-start-12) because str only allows for unscaled
1376 // 9-bit immediate offset [-256,256]. If start is large enough, which can
1377 // happen when a function has many params (>=32 i64), str cannot be encoded
1378 // properly. We can use Str, which will generate more instructions, so
1379 // fallback to the general case below.
1380 if (size <= 12 * kStackSlotSize &&
1381 IsImmLSPair(max_stp_offset, kXRegSizeLog2) &&
1382 IsImmLSUnscaled(-start - 12)) {
1383 // Special straight-line code for up to 12 slots. Generates one
1384 // instruction per two slots (<= 7 instructions total).
1385 static_assert(kStackSlotSize == kSystemPointerSize);
1386 uint32_t remainder = size;
1387 for (; remainder >= 2 * kStackSlotSize; remainder -= 2 * kStackSlotSize) {
1388 stp(xzr, xzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1389 }
1390
1391 DCHECK_GE(12, remainder);
1392 switch (remainder) {
1393 case 12:
1394 str(xzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1395 str(wzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder - 8));
1396 break;
1397 case 8:
1398 str(xzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1399 break;
1400 case 4:
1401 str(wzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1402 break;
1403 case 0:
1404 break;
1405 default:
1406 UNREACHABLE();
1407 }
1408 } else {
1409 // General case for bigger counts (5-8 instructions).
1410 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1411 Register address_reg = temps.AcquireX();
1412 // This {Sub} might use another temp register if the offset is too large.
1413 Sub(address_reg, fp, start + size);
1414 Register count_reg = temps.AcquireX();
1415 Mov(count_reg, size / 4);
1416
1417 Label loop;
1418 bind(&loop);
1419 sub(count_reg, count_reg, 1);
1420 str(wzr, MemOperand(address_reg, kSystemPointerSize / 2, PostIndex));
1421 cbnz(count_reg, &loop);
1422 }
1423}
1424
1425void LiftoffAssembler::LoadSpillAddress(Register dst, int offset,
1426 ValueKind /* kind */) {
1427 Sub(dst, fp, offset);
1428}

1735
1736void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
1737 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1738 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1739 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1740 Register scratch = temps.AcquireW();
1741 Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1742 Add(scratch, scratch, Operand(Smi::FromInt(1)));
1743 Str(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1744 } else {
1745 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
1746 SmiUntag(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1747 Add(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
1748 SmiTag(scratch);
1749 Str(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1750 }
1751}
1752
1753void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divs(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1754 Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1755 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1756 Register dst_w = dst.W();
1757 Register lhs_w = lhs.W();
1758 Register rhs_w = rhs.W();
1759 bool can_use_dst = !dst_w.Aliases(lhs_w) && !dst_w.Aliases(rhs_w);
1760 if (can_use_dst) {
1761 // Do div early.
1762 Sdiv(dst_w, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1763 }
1764 // Check for division by zero.
1765 Cbz(rhs_w, trap_div_by_zero);
1766 // Check for kMinInt / -1. This is unrepresentable.
1767 Cmp(rhs_w, -1);
1768 Ccmp(lhs_w, 1, NoFlag, eq);
1769 B(trap_div_unrepresentable, vs);
1770 if (!can_use_dst) {
1771 // Do div.
1772 Sdiv(dst_w, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1773 }
1774}
1775
1776void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1777 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1778 // Check for division by zero.
1779 Cbz(rhs.W(), trap_div_by_zero);
1780 // Do div.
1781 Udiv(dst.W(), lhs.W(), rhs.W());
1782}
1783
1784void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_rems(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1785 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1786 Register dst_w = dst.W();
1787 Register lhs_w = lhs.W();
1788 Register rhs_w = rhs.W();
1789 // Do early div.
1790 // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
1791 // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
1792 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1793 Register scratch = temps.AcquireW();
1794 Sdiv(scratch, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1795 // Check for division by zero.
1796 Cbz(rhs_w, trap_div_by_zero);
1797 // Compute remainder.
1798 Msub(dst_w, scratch, rhs_w, lhs_w);
1799}
1800
1801void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_remu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1802 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1803 Register dst_w = dst.W();
1804 Register lhs_w = lhs.W();
1805 Register rhs_w = rhs.W();
1806 // Do early div.
1807 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1808 Register scratch = temps.AcquireW();
1809 Udiv(scratch, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1810 // Check for division by zero.
1811 Cbz(rhs_w, trap_div_by_zero);
1812 // Compute remainder.
1813 Msub(dst_w, scratch, rhs_w, lhs_w);
1814}
1815
1816bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_divs(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1817 LiftoffRegister rhs,
1818 Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1819 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1820 Register dst_x = dst.gp().X();
1821 Register lhs_x = lhs.gp().X();
1822 Register rhs_x = rhs.gp().X();
1823 bool can_use_dst = !dst_x.Aliases(lhs_x) && !dst_x.Aliases(rhs_x);
1824 if (can_use_dst) {
1825 // Do div early.
1826 Sdiv(dst_x, lhs_x, rhs_x);
1827 }
1828 // Check for division by zero.
1829 Cbz(rhs_x, trap_div_by_zero);
1830 // Check for kMinInt / -1. This is unrepresentable.
1831 Cmp(rhs_x, -1);
1832 Ccmp(lhs_x, 1, NoFlag, eq);
1833 B(trap_div_unrepresentable, vs);
1834 if (!can_use_dst) {
1835 // Do div.
1836 Sdiv(dst_x, lhs_x, rhs_x);
1837 }
1838 return true;
1839}
1840
1841bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_divu(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1842 LiftoffRegister rhs,
1843 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1844 // Check for division by zero.
1845 Cbz(rhs.gp().X(), trap_div_by_zero);
1846 // Do div.
1847 Udiv(dst.gp().X(), lhs.gp().X(), rhs.gp().X());
1848 return true;
1849}
1850
1851bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_rems(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1852 LiftoffRegister rhs,
1853 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1854 Register dst_x = dst.gp().X();
1855 Register lhs_x = lhs.gp().X();
1856 Register rhs_x = rhs.gp().X();
1857 // Do early div.
1858 // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
1859 // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
1860 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1861 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
1862 Sdiv(scratch, lhs_x, rhs_x);
1863 // Check for division by zero.
1864 Cbz(rhs_x, trap_div_by_zero);
1865 // Compute remainder.
1866 Msub(dst_x, scratch, rhs_x, lhs_x);
1867 return true;
1868}
1869
1870bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_remu(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1871 LiftoffRegister rhs,
1872 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1873 Register dst_x = dst.gp().X();
1874 Register lhs_x = lhs.gp().X();
1875 Register rhs_x = rhs.gp().X();
1876 // Do early div.
1877 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1878 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
1879 Udiv(scratch, lhs_x, rhs_x);
1880 // Check for division by zero.
1881 Cbz(rhs_x, trap_div_by_zero);
1882 // Compute remainder.
1883 Msub(dst_x, scratch, rhs_x, lhs_x);
1884 return true;
1885}

1887void LiftoffAssembler::emit_u32_to_uintptr(Register dst, Register src) {
1888 Uxtw(dst, src);
1889}
1890
1891void LiftoffAssembler::clear_i32_upper_half(Register dst) { Uxtw(dst, dst); }
1892
1893void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
1894 DoubleRegister rhs) {
1895 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1896 DoubleRegister scratch = temps.AcquireD();
1897 Ushr(scratch.V2S(), rhs.V2S(), 31);
1898 if (dst != lhs) {
1899 Fmov(dst.S(), lhs.S());
1900 }
1901 Sli(dst.V2S(), scratch.V2S(), 31);
1902}
1903
1904void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
1905 DoubleRegister rhs) {
1906 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1907 DoubleRegister scratch = temps.AcquireD();
1908 Ushr(scratch.V1D(), rhs.V1D(), 63);
1909 if (dst != lhs) {
1910 Fmov(dst.D(), lhs.D());
1911 }
1912 Sli(dst.V1D(), scratch.V1D(), 63);
1913}
1914
1915bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
1916 LiftoffRegister dst,
1917 LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
1918 switch (opcode) {
1919 case kExprI32ConvertI64:
1920 Mov(dst.gp().W(), src.gp().W());
1921 return true;
1922 case kExprI32SConvertF32:
1923 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
1924 // Check underflow and NaN.
1925 Fcmp(src.fp().S(), static_cast<float>(INT32_MIN));
1926 // Check overflow.
1927 Ccmp(dst.gp().W(), -1, VFlag, ge);
1928 B(trap, vs);
1929 return true;
1930 case kExprI32UConvertF32:
1931 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
1932 // Check underflow and NaN.
1933 Fcmp(src.fp().S(), -1.0);
1934 // Check overflow.
1935 Ccmp(dst.gp().W(), -1, ZFlag, gt);
1936 B(trap, eq);
1937 return true;
1938 case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
1939 // INT32_MIN and INT32_MAX are valid results, we cannot test the result
1940 // to detect the overflows. We could have done two immediate floating
1941 // point comparisons but it would have generated two conditional branches.
1942 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1943 VRegister fp_ref = temps.AcquireD();
1944 VRegister fp_cmp = temps.AcquireD();
1945 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
1946 Frintz(fp_ref, src.fp().D()); // f64 -> f64 round to zero.
1947 Scvtf(fp_cmp, dst.gp().W()); // i32 -> f64.
1948 // If comparison fails, we have an overflow or a NaN.
1949 Fcmp(fp_cmp, fp_ref);
1950 B(trap, ne);
1951 return true;
1952 }
1953 case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
1954 // INT32_MAX is a valid result, we cannot test the result to detect the
1955 // overflows. We could have done two immediate floating point comparisons
1956 // but it would have generated two conditional branches.
1957 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1958 VRegister fp_ref = temps.AcquireD();
1959 VRegister fp_cmp = temps.AcquireD();
1960 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
1961 Frintz(fp_ref, src.fp().D()); // f64 -> f64 round to zero.
1962 Ucvtf(fp_cmp, dst.gp().W()); // i32 -> f64.
1963 // If comparison fails, we have an overflow or a NaN.
1964 Fcmp(fp_cmp, fp_ref);
1965 B(trap, ne);
1966 return true;
1967 }
1968 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1969 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S());
1970 return true;
1971 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1972 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S());
1973 return true;
1974 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1975 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D());
1976 return true;
1977 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1978 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D());
1979 return true;
1980 case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1981 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S());
1982 return true;
1983 case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1984 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S());
1985 return true;
1986 case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1987 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D());
1988 return true;
1989 case kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1990 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D());
1991 return true;
1992 case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
1993 Fmov(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S());
1994 return true;
1995 case kExprI64SConvertI32:
1996 Sxtw(dst.gp().X(), src.gp().W());
1997 return true;
1998 case kExprI64SConvertF32:
1999 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i64 round to zero.
2000 // Check underflow and NaN.
2001 Fcmp(src.fp().S(), static_cast<float>(INT64_MIN));
2002 // Check overflow.
2003 Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, VFlag, ge);
2004 B(trap, vs);
2005 return true;
2006 case kExprI64UConvertF32:
2007 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i64 round to zero.
2008 // Check underflow and NaN.
2009 Fcmp(src.fp().S(), -1.0);
2010 // Check overflow.
2011 Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, ZFlag, gt);
2012 B(trap, eq);
2013 return true;
2014 case kExprI64SConvertF64:
2015 Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i64 round to zero.
2016 // Check underflow and NaN.
2017 Fcmp(src.fp().D(), static_cast<float>(INT64_MIN));
2018 // Check overflow.
2019 Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, VFlag, ge);
2020 B(trap, vs);
2021 return true;
2022 case kExprI64UConvertF64:
2023 Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i64 round to zero.
2024 // Check underflow and NaN.
2025 Fcmp(src.fp().D(), -1.0);
2026 // Check overflow.
2027 Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, ZFlag, gt);
2028 B(trap, eq);
2029 return true;
2030 case kExprI64UConvertI32:
2031 Mov(dst.gp().W(), src.gp().W());
2032 return true;
2033 case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
2034 Fmov(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D());
2035 return true;
2036 case kExprF32SConvertI32:
2037 Scvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().W());
2038 return true;
2039 case kExprF32UConvertI32:
2040 Ucvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().W());
2041 return true;
2042 case kExprF32SConvertI64:
2043 Scvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().X());
2044 return true;
2045 case kExprF32UConvertI64:
2046 Ucvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().X());
2047 return true;
2048 case kExprF32ConvertF64:
2049 Fcvt(dst.fp().S(), src.fp().D());
2050 return true;
2051 case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
2052 Fmov(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().W());
2053 return true;
2054 case kExprF64SConvertI32:
2055 Scvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().W());
2056 return true;
2057 case kExprF64UConvertI32:
2058 Ucvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().W());
2059 return true;
2060 case kExprF64SConvertI64:
2061 Scvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().X());
2062 return true;
2063 case kExprF64UConvertI64:
2064 Ucvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().X());
2065 return true;
2066 case kExprF64ConvertF32:
2067 Fcvt(dst.fp().D(), src.fp().S());
2068 return true;
2069 case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
2070 Fmov(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().X());
2071 return true;
2072 default:
2073 UNREACHABLE();
2074 }
2075}

2100void LiftoffAssembler::emit_jump(Label* label) { B(label); }
2101
2102void LiftoffAssembler::emit_jump(Register target) { Br(target); }
2103
2104void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
2105 ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
2106 Register rhs,
2107 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2108 switch (kind) {
2109 case kI32:
2110 if (rhs.is_valid()) {
2111 Cmp(lhs.W(), rhs.W());
2112 } else {
2113 Cmp(lhs.W(), wzr);
2114 }
2115 break;
2116 case kRef:
2117 case kRefNull:
2118 case kRtt:
2119 DCHECK(rhs.is_valid());
2120 DCHECK(cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual);
2121#if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
2122 Cmp(lhs.W(), rhs.W());
2123#else
2124 Cmp(lhs.X(), rhs.X());
2125#endif
2126 break;
2127 case kI64:
2128 if (rhs.is_valid()) {
2129 Cmp(lhs.X(), rhs.X());
2130 } else {
2131 Cmp(lhs.X(), xzr);
2132 }
2133 break;
2134 default:
2135 UNREACHABLE();
2136 }
2137 B(label, cond);
2138}
2139
2140void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_cond_jumpi(Condition cond, Label* label,
2141 Register lhs, int32_t imm,
2142 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2143 Cmp(lhs.W(), Operand(imm));
2144 B(label, cond);
2145}
2146
2147void LiftoffAssembler::emit_ptrsize_cond_jumpi(Condition cond, Label* label,
2148 Register lhs, int32_t imm,
2149 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2150 Cmp(lhs.X(), Operand(imm));
2151 B(label, cond);
2152}

2177void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2178 DoubleRegister lhs,
2179 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2180 Fcmp(lhs.S(), rhs.S());
2181 Cset(dst.W(), cond);
2182 if (cond != ne) {
2183 // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2184 Csel(dst.W(), wzr, dst.W(), vs);
2185 }
2186}

2193 if (cond != ne) {
2194 // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2195 Csel(dst.W(), wzr, dst.W(), vs);
2196 }
2197}
2198
2199bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_select(LiftoffRegister dst, Register condition,
2200 LiftoffRegister true_value,
2201 LiftoffRegister false_value,
2202 ValueKind kind) {
2203 if (kind != kI32 && kind != kI64 && kind != kF32 && kind != kF64)
2204 return false;
2205
2206 Cmp(condition.W(), wzr);
2207 switch (kind) {
2208 default:
2209 UNREACHABLE();
2210 case kI32:
2211 Csel(dst.gp().W(), true_value.gp().W(), false_value.gp().W(), ne);
2212 break;
2213 case kI64:
2214 Csel(dst.gp().X(), true_value.gp().X(), false_value.gp().X(), ne);
2215 break;
2216 case kF32:
2217 Fcsel(dst.fp().S(), true_value.fp().S(), false_value.fp().S(), ne);
2218 break;
2219 case kF64:
2220 Fcsel(dst.fp().D(), true_value.fp().D(), false_value.fp().D(), ne);
2221 break;
2222 }
2223 return true;
2224}
2225
2226void LiftoffAssembler::emit_smi_check(Register obj, Label* target,
2227 SmiCheckMode mode,
2228 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2229 Label* smi_label = mode == kJumpOnSmi ? target : nullptr;
2230 Label* not_smi_label = mode == kJumpOnNotSmi ? target : nullptr;
2231 JumpIfSmi(obj, smi_label, not_smi_label);
2232}
2233
2234void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2235 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2236 LoadType type,
2237 LoadTransformationKind transform,
2238 uint32_t* protected_load_pc) {
2239 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2240 MemOperand src_op =
2241 transform == LoadTransformationKind::kSplat
2242 ? MemOperand{liftoff::GetEffectiveAddress(this, &temps, src_addr,
2243 offset_reg, offset_imm)}
2244 : liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
2245 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2246 MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2247
2248 if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2249 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2250 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2251 Sxtl(dst.fp().V8H(), dst.fp().V8B());
2252 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2253 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2254 Uxtl(dst.fp().V8H(), dst.fp().V8B());
2255 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2256 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2257 Sxtl(dst.fp().V4S(), dst.fp().V4H());
2258 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2259 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2260 Uxtl(dst.fp().V4S(), dst.fp().V4H());
2261 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2262 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2263 Sxtl(dst.fp().V2D(), dst.fp().V2S());
2264 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2265 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2266 Uxtl(dst.fp().V2D(), dst.fp().V2S());
2267 }
2268 } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2269 if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2270 Ldr(dst.fp().S(), src_op);
2271 } else {
2272 DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2273 Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2274 }
2275 } else {
2276 DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2277 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2278 ld1r(dst.fp().V16B(), src_op);
2279 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2280 ld1r(dst.fp().V8H(), src_op);
2281 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2282 ld1r(dst.fp().V4S(), src_op);
2283 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2284 ld1r(dst.fp().V2D(), src_op);
2285 }
2286 }
2287}
2288
2289void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2290 Register addr, Register offset_reg,
2291 uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
2292 uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2293 bool i64_offset) {
2294 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2295 MemOperand src_op{liftoff::GetEffectiveAddress(this, &temps, addr, offset_reg,
2296 offset_imm, i64_offset)};
2297
2298 MachineType mem_type = type.mem_type();
2299 if (dst != src) {
2300 Mov(dst.fp().Q(), src.fp().Q());
2301 }
2302
2303 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2304 if (mem_type == MachineType::Int8()) {
2305 ld1(dst.fp().B(), laneidx, src_op);
2306 } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int16()) {
2307 ld1(dst.fp().H(), laneidx, src_op);
2308 } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int32()) {
2309 ld1(dst.fp().S(), laneidx, src_op);
2310 } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int64()) {
2311 ld1(dst.fp().D(), laneidx, src_op);
2312 } else {
2313 UNREACHABLE();
2314 }
2315}
2316
2317void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,
2318 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
2319 StoreType type, uint8_t lane,
2320 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
2321 bool i64_offset) {
2322 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2323 MemOperand dst_op{liftoff::GetEffectiveAddress(this, &temps, dst, offset,
2324 offset_imm, i64_offset)};
2325 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
2326
2327 MachineRepresentation rep = type.mem_rep();
2328 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
2329 st1(src.fp().B(), lane, dst_op);
2330 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
2331 st1(src.fp().H(), lane, dst_op);
2332 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
2333 st1(src.fp().S(), lane, dst_op);
2334 } else {
2335 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kWord64, rep);
2336 st1(src.fp().D(), lane, dst_op);
2337 }
2338}

2409void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_neg(LiftoffRegister dst,

2472
2473void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_pmin(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2474 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2475 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2476
2477 VRegister tmp = dst.fp();
2478 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
2479 tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat2D);
2480 }
2481
2482 Fcmgt(tmp.V2D(), lhs.fp().V2D(), rhs.fp().V2D());
2483 Bsl(tmp.V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B(), lhs.fp().V16B());
2484
2485 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
2486 Mov(dst.fp().V2D(), tmp);
2487 }
2488}
2489
2490void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_pmax(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2491 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2492 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2493
2494 VRegister tmp = dst.fp();
2495 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
2496 tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat2D);
2497 }
2498
2499 Fcmgt(tmp.V2D(), rhs.fp().V2D(), lhs.fp().V2D());
2500 Bsl(tmp.V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B(), lhs.fp().V16B());
2501
2502 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
2503 Mov(dst.fp().V2D(), tmp);
2504 }
2505}

2752
2753void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2754 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2755 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2756 VRegister tmp1 = temps.AcquireV(kFormat2D);
2757 VRegister tmp2 = temps.AcquireV(kFormat2D);
2758
2759 // Algorithm copied from code-generator-arm64.cc with minor modifications:
2760 // - 2 (max number of scratch registers in Liftoff) temporaries instead of 3
2761 // - 1 more Umull instruction to calculate | cg | ae |,
2762 // - so, we can no longer use Umlal in the last step, and use Add instead.
2763 // Refer to comments there for details.
2764 Xtn(tmp1.V2S(), lhs.fp().V2D());
2765 Xtn(tmp2.V2S(), rhs.fp().V2D());
2766 Umull(tmp1.V2D(), tmp1.V2S(), tmp2.V2S());
2767 Rev64(tmp2.V4S(), rhs.fp().V4S());
2768 Mul(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), lhs.fp().V4S());
2769 Addp(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S());
2770 Shll(dst.fp().V2D(), tmp2.V2S(), 32);
2771 Add(dst.fp().V2D(), dst.fp().V2D(), tmp1.V2D());
2772}
2773

2776 LiftoffRegister src2) {

2938void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_dot_i16x8_s(LiftoffRegister dst,
2939 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2940 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2941 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(this);
2942 VRegister tmp1 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat4S);
2943 VRegister tmp2 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat4S);
2944 Smull(tmp1, lhs.fp().V4H(), rhs.fp().V4H());
2945 Smull2(tmp2, lhs.fp().V8H(), rhs.fp().V8H());
2946 Addp(dst.fp().V4S(), tmp1, tmp2);
2947}

3127
3128void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
3129 LiftoffRegister lhs,
3130 LiftoffRegister rhs,
3131 const uint8_t shuffle[16],
3132 bool is_swizzle) {
3133 VRegister src1 = lhs.fp();
3134 VRegister src2 = rhs.fp();
3135 VRegister temp = dst.fp();
3136 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3137 // dst overlaps with lhs or rhs, so we need a temporary.
3138 temp = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs}).fp();
3139 }
3140
3141 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(this);
3142
3143 if (src1 != src2 && !AreConsecutive(src1, src2)) {
3144 // Tbl needs consecutive registers, which our scratch registers are.
3145 src1 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat16B);
3146 src2 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat16B);
3147 DCHECK(AreConsecutive(src1, src2));
3148 Mov(src1.Q(), lhs.fp().Q());
3149 Mov(src2.Q(), rhs.fp().Q());
3150 }
3151
3152 int64_t imms[2] = {0, 0};
3153 for (int i = 7; i >= 0; i--) {
3154 imms[0] = (imms[0] << 8) | (shuffle[i]);
3155 imms[1] = (imms[1] << 8) | (shuffle[i + 8]);
3156 }
3157 DCHECK_EQ(0, (imms[0] | imms[1]) &
3158 (lhs == rhs ? 0xF0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0 : 0xE0E0E0E0E0E0E0E0));
3159
3160 Movi(temp.V16B(), imms[1], imms[0]);
3161
3162 if (src1 == src2) {
3163 Tbl(dst.fp().V16B(), src1.V16B(), temp.V16B());
3164 } else {
3165 Tbl(dst.fp().V16B(), src1.V16B(), src2.V16B(), temp.V16B());
3166 }
3167}

3542void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_sconvert_i16x8(LiftoffRegister dst,
3543 LiftoffRegister lhs,
3544 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3545 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3546 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3547 VRegister right = rhs.fp().V8H();
3548 if (dst == rhs) {
3549 Mov(tmp, right);
3550 right = tmp;
3551 }
3552 Sqxtn(dst.fp().V8B(), lhs.fp().V8H());
3553 Sqxtn2(dst.fp().V16B(), right);
3554}

3563 Mov(tmp, right);
3564 right = tmp;
3565 }
3566 Sqxtun(dst.fp().V8B(), lhs.fp().V8H());
3567 Sqxtun2(dst.fp().V16B(), right);
3568}

3724void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_dot_i8x16_i7x16_s(LiftoffRegister dst,
3725 LiftoffRegister lhs,
3726 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3727 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(this);
3728 VRegister tmp1 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3729 VRegister tmp2 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3730 Smull(tmp1, lhs.fp().V8B(), rhs.fp().V8B());
3731 Smull2(tmp2, lhs.fp().V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B());
3732 Addp(dst.fp().V8H(), tmp1, tmp2);
3733}
3734
3735void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_dot_i8x16_i7x16_add_s(LiftoffRegister dst,
3736 LiftoffRegister lhs,
3737 LiftoffRegister rhs,
3738 LiftoffRegister acc) {
3739 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(this);
3740 VRegister tmp1 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3741 VRegister tmp2 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3742 Smull(tmp1, lhs.fp().V8B(), rhs.fp().V8B());
3743 Smull2(tmp2, lhs.fp().V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B());
3744 Addp(tmp1, tmp1, tmp2);
3745 Saddlp(tmp1.V4S(), tmp1);
3746 Add(dst.fp().V4S(), tmp1.V4S(), acc.fp().V4S());
3747}

3758
3759#define EMIT_QFMOP(instr, format) \
3760 if (dst == src3) { \
3761 instr(dst.fp().V##format(), src1.fp().V##format(), src2.fp().V##format()); \
3762 } else if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) { \
3763 Mov(dst.fp().V##format(), src3.fp().V##format()); \
3764 instr(dst.fp().V##format(), src1.fp().V##format(), src2.fp().V##format()); \
3765 } else { \
3766 DCHECK(dst == src1 || dst == src2); \
3767 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this); \
3768 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat##format); \
3769 Mov(tmp, src3.fp().V##format()); \
3770 instr(tmp, src1.fp().V##format(), src2.fp().V##format()); \
3771 Mov(dst.fp().V##format(), tmp); \
3772 }
3773
3774bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_qfma(LiftoffRegister dst,
3775 LiftoffRegister src1,
3776 LiftoffRegister src2,
3777 LiftoffRegister src3) {
3778 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
3779 return false;
3780 }
3781 EMIT_QFMOP(Fmla, 8H);
3782 return true;
3783}
3784
3785bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_qfms(LiftoffRegister dst,

3787 LiftoffRegister src2,
3788 LiftoffRegister src3) {
3789 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
3790 return false;
3791 }
3792 EMIT_QFMOP(Fmls, 8H);

3826bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_splat(LiftoffRegister dst,
3827 LiftoffRegister src) {
3828 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
3829 return false;
3830 }
3831 Fcvt(dst.fp().H(), src.fp().S());
3832 Dup(dst.fp().V8H(), dst.fp().H(), 0);
3833 return true;
3834}

3836bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_extract_lane(LiftoffRegister dst,
3837 LiftoffRegister lhs,
3838 uint8_t imm_lane_idx) {
3839 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
3840 return false;
3841 }
3842 Mov(dst.fp().H(), lhs.fp().V8H(), imm_lane_idx);
3843 Fcvt(dst.fp().S(), dst.fp().H());
3844 return true;
3845}
3846
3847bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_replace_lane(LiftoffRegister dst,
3848 LiftoffRegister src1,
3849 LiftoffRegister src2,
3850 uint8_t imm_lane_idx) {
3851 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
3852 return false;
3853 }
3854 if (dst != src1) {
3855 Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), src1.fp().V8H());
3856 }
3857 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3858
3859 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3860 Fcvt(tmp.H(), src2.fp().S());
3861 Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), imm_lane_idx, tmp.V8H(), 0);
3862 return true;
3863}

3986 return false;

3988 Fmul(dst.fp().V8H(), lhs.fp().V8H(), rhs.fp().V8H());
3989 return true;
3990}

4018
4019bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_pmin(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
4020 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
4021 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
4022 return false;
4023 }
4024 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4025
4026 VRegister tmp = dst.fp();
4027 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
4028 tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
4029 }
4030
4031 Fcmgt(tmp.V8H(), lhs.fp().V8H(), rhs.fp().V8H());
4032 Bsl(tmp.V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B(), lhs.fp().V16B());
4033
4034 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
4035 Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), tmp);
4036 }
4037 return true;
4038}
4039
4040bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_pmax(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
4041 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
4042 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
4043 return false;
4044 }
4045 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4046
4047 VRegister tmp = dst.fp();
4048 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
4049 tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
4050 }
4051
4052 Fcmgt(tmp.V8H(), rhs.fp().V8H(), lhs.fp().V8H());
4053 Bsl(tmp.V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B(), lhs.fp().V16B());
4054
4055 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
4056 Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), tmp);
4057 }
4058 return true;
4059}

4105
4106bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_demote_f64x2_zero(LiftoffRegister dst,
4107 LiftoffRegister src) {
4108 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
4109 return false;
4110 }
4111 // There is no vector f64 -> f16 conversion instruction,
4112 // so convert them by component using scalar version.
4113 // Convert high double to a temp reg first, because dst and src
4114 // can overlap.
4115 Mov(fp_scratch.D(), src.fp().V2D(), 1);
4116 Fcvt(fp_scratch.H(), fp_scratch.D());
4117
4118 Fcvt(dst.fp().H(), src.fp().D());
4119 Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), 1, fp_scratch.V8H(), 0);
4120 return true;
4121}

4142void LiftoffAssembler::StackCheck(Label* ool_code) {
4143 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4144 Register limit_address = temps.AcquireX();
4145 LoadStackLimit(limit_address, StackLimitKind::kInterruptStackLimit);
4146 Cmp(sp, limit_address);
4147 B(ool_code, ls);
4148}

4163
4164void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
4165 SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
4166 LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
4167 LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
4168 int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
4169 LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
4170 bool needs_padding = (gp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() & 1) != 0;
4171 if (needs_padding) {
4172 spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
4173 ++spill_offset;
4174 }
4175 while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
4176 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetLastRegSet();
4177 if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
4178 safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
4179 }
4180 gp_spills.clear(reg);
4181 ++spill_offset;
4182 spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
4183 }
4184 // Record the number of additional spill slots.
4185 RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
4186}
4187
4188void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
4189 DropSlots(num_stack_slots);
4190 Ret();
4191}
4192
4193void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
4194 const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
4195 ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
4196 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4197 // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
4198 int total_size = RoundUp(stack_bytes, kQuadWordSizeInBytes);
4199 // Reserve space in the stack.
4200 Claim(total_size, 1);
4201
4202 int arg_offset = 0;
4203 for (const VarState& arg : args) {
4204 liftoff::StoreToMemory(this, MemOperand{sp, arg_offset}, arg);
4205 arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
4206 }
4207 DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
4208
4209 // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function.
4210 Mov(x0, sp);
4211
4212 // Now call the C function.
4213 constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
4214 CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
4215
4216 // Move return value to the right register.
4217 const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
4218 if (return_kind != kVoid) {
4219 constexpr Register kReturnReg = x0;
4220 if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
4221 Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
4222 }
4223 ++next_result_reg;
4224 }
4225
4226 // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
4227 if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
4228 if (out_argument_kind == kI16) {
4229 Ldrh(next_result_reg->gp(), MemOperand(sp));
4230 } else {
4231 Peek(liftoff::GetRegFromType(*next_result_reg, out_argument_kind), 0);
4232 }
4233 }
4234
4235 Drop(total_size, 1);
4236}
4237
4238void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args_list,
4239 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4240 const int num_args = static_cast<int>(args_list.size());
4241 const VarState* const args = args_list.begin();
4242
4243 // Note: If we ever need more than eight arguments we would need to load the
4244 // stack arguments to registers (via LoadToRegister) in pairs of two, then use
4245 // Stp with MemOperand{sp, -2 * kSystemPointerSize, PreIndex} to push them to
4246 // the stack.
4247
4248 // Execute the parallel register move for register parameters.
4249 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(kCArgRegs), num_args);
4250 ParallelMove parallel_move{this};
4251 for (int reg_arg = 0; reg_arg < num_args; ++reg_arg) {
4252 parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(LiftoffRegister{kCArgRegs[reg_arg]},
4253 args[reg_arg]);
4254 }
4255 parallel_move.Execute();
4256
4257 // Now call the C function.
4258 CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_args);
4259}

4268
4269void LiftoffAssembler::CallIndirect(const ValueKindSig* sig,
4270 compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
4271 Register target) {
4272 // For Arm64, we have more cache registers than wasm parameters. That means
4273 // that target will always be in a register.
4274 DCHECK(target.is_valid());
4275 CallWasmCodePointer(target, call_descriptor->signature_hash());
4276}
4277
4278void LiftoffAssembler::TailCallIndirect(
4279 compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, Register target) {
4280 DCHECK(target.is_valid());
4281 // When control flow integrity is enabled, the target is a "bti c"
4282 // instruction, which enforces that the jump instruction is either a "blr", or
4283 // a "br" with x16 or x17 as its destination.
4284 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4285 temps.Exclude(x17);
4286 Mov(x17, target);
4287 CallWasmCodePointer(x17, call_descriptor->signature_hash(),
4288 CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
4289}

4291void LiftoffAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
4292 // A direct call to a builtin. Just encode the builtin index. This will be
4293 // patched at relocation.
4294 Call(static_cast<Address>(builtin), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
4295}

4311
4312void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4313 DoubleRegister src,
4314 ValueKind kind) {
4315 Label not_nan;
4316 if (kind == kF32) {
4317 Fcmp(src.S(), src.S());
4318 B(eq, &not_nan); // x != x iff isnan(x)
4319 // If it's a NaN, it must be non-zero, so store that as the set value.
4320 Str(src.S(), MemOperand(dst));
4321 } else {
4322 DCHECK_EQ(kind, kF64);
4323 Fcmp(src.D(), src.D());
4324 B(eq, &not_nan); // x != x iff isnan(x)
4325 // Double-precision NaNs must be non-zero in the most-significant 32
4326 // bits, so store that.
4327 St1(src.V4S(), 1, MemOperand(dst));
4328 }
4329 Bind(&not_nan);
4330}
4331
4332void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4333 LiftoffRegister src,
4334 Register tmp_gp,
4335 LiftoffRegister tmp_s128,
4336 ValueKind lane_kind) {
4337 DoubleRegister tmp_fp = tmp_s128.fp();
4338 if (lane_kind == kF32) {
4339 Fmaxv(tmp_fp.S(), src.fp().V4S());
4340 } else {
4341 DCHECK_EQ(lane_kind, kF64);
4342 Fmaxp(tmp_fp.D(), src.fp().V2D());
4343 }
4344 emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(dst, tmp_fp, lane_kind);
4345}
4346
4347void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero(Register dst) {
4348 Str(dst, MemOperand(dst));
4349}
4350
4351void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
4352 DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
4353 // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
4354 asm_->Claim(RoundUp(param_slots, 2));
4355 for (auto& slot : slots_) {
4356 int poke_offset = slot.dst_slot_ * kSystemPointerSize;
4357 switch (slot.src_.loc()) {
4358 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack: {
4359 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
4360 CPURegister scratch = liftoff::AcquireByType(&temps, slot.src_.kind());
4361 asm_->Ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
4362 asm_->Poke(scratch, poke_offset);
4363 break;
4364 }
4365 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister:
4366 asm_->Poke(liftoff::GetRegFromType(slot.src_.reg(), slot.src_.kind()),
4367 poke_offset);
4368 break;
4369 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst:
4370 DCHECK(slot.src_.kind() == kI32 || slot.src_.kind() == kI64);
4371 if (slot.src_.i32_const() == 0) {
4372 Register zero_reg = slot.src_.kind() == kI32 ? wzr : xzr;
4373 asm_->Poke(zero_reg, poke_offset);
4374 } else {
4375 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
4376 Register scratch =
4377 slot.src_.kind() == kI32 ? temps.AcquireW() : temps.AcquireX();
4378 asm_->Mov(scratch, int64_t{slot.src_.i32_const()});
4379 asm_->Poke(scratch, poke_offset);
4380 }
4381 break;
4382 }
4383 }
4384}
